node.title: NSW reaches 90 per cent fully vaccinated target
node.alt: Socially distanced people outside a vaccination clinic, having their details checked by people in hi-vis vests
node.description: NSW reaches the 90 per cent double-dose vaccination milestone for people over age 16, a day after more freedoms were rolled out.
node.content:
["NSW has reached\u00a0the 90 per cent double-dose vaccination milestone\u00a0for people over the age of 16, a day after more freedoms were rolled out.", "The latest data from the federal government's Operation COVID Shield also showed\u00a0the percentage of those who were partially vaccinated\u00a0had\u00a0jumped to 94 per cent.", "After hearing the news NSW Premier Dominic Perrottet told Parliament: \"I want to pay tribute to the Health Minister and the health teams as we lead the nation out of this pandemic.\"", "The vaccination milestone comes a day after the state brought forward its pandemic recovery roadmap, which lifted caps on home visitors and allowed for dancing and singing in nightclubs.", "Those yet to receive both shots\u00a0will need to wait until December 15 or until the state hits its 95 per cent target, whichever comes first.", "The state\u00a0recorded 222\u00a0locally acquired infections and four deaths in the 24 hours to 8.00pm last night.", "There are now 254\u00a0people in hospital and 42 of those are in intensive care.", "Official health data released yesterday\u00a0revealed that unvaccinated people in NSW were 16 times more likely to die, or end up in intensive care, during the Delta outbreak.", "COVID-19 ICU admissions or deaths peaked between September 8 and September 21, with\u00a0just 0.9 per 100,000 fully vaccinated people, compared to\u00a015.6 per 100,000 who were unvaccinated.", "Most positive cases from between June 16 and October 7 were also\u00a0unvaccinated.", "More to come.", "", "
